min and max in sql
-----------------------------
The min() function returns the smallest value of the selected column.

The max() function returns the larges value of the selected column.

usage:

select min(column_name) from table_name;

count()
-----------------------------

The count() function returns the number of rows that matches the certain condition if there no condition it returns the number of rows.

avg() -> returns the average for the column

sum() -> returns the sum for the column
